Well, here is my little theory about the story. As an agnostic, i decided to left the mystical things of Matrix and consider the problem in the computer side.<br>
<br>
Let us see the Matrix as a sphere, it's the inner Matrix. As most of computer programs, there are bugs. So we need to redirect exceptions of this program somewhere &quot;Real World&quot; which is a a layer of our sphere. When Neo at the end can feel the sentinels, he says &quot;Something is different&quot; and stop them. He knows now that he is in another matrix and become an exception of this second matrix. So the system throw him off this layer to a third layer or the real &quot;Real world&quot;.<br>
<br>
Now the &quot;Why?&quot; Suppose you want to find someone &quot;special&quot; between billions of individuals. You create a trial &quot;the matrix&quot;. Now you create a wonderful story with Oracle, Prophecy etc.... Only people who success this trial will be allowed to go to level 2 &quot;Zion&quot;. This second trial will be more difficult (life conditions are really awful) so you will find your elite then bingo level .<br>
<br>
In the film at the end Neo and Smith are in coma, they are the only ones who understood that it wasnt the real world.<br>
<br>
I know my explanations arent very clear. But consider architect and oracle as Operating system, they have CONTROL. The only thing im not sure is about Ghost, he is near Neo in power, and appear as gold code when Neo look at him (maybe a programmer? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
<br>
I think Warshowsky brothers want to fool us with mystical things, dont forget Matrix is control over mind, oracle is constantly manipulating Neo, Morpheus and Trinity, and i think they try to control us to make us look at a direction and they will surprise us with the end, and i love that idea.<br>
<br>
What do you think if it's only  a video game at the end ? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
