<br>
I don't think that Zion exists in another Matrix on top of the Matrix that they are freed from, for two reasons:  1) some Matrix insiders, including Joel Silver I believe, said there are no &quot;boxes in boxes&quot; and 2) if the &quot;Real World&quot; was just more programming, Smith would have replicated himself and/or changed his appearance to that of Smith.<br>
<br>
In the &quot;Real World&quot; Smith is constrained by the realities of physicality and cannot change things as he does in the world of the Matrix.<br>
<br>
As for the relationship between the Oracle and the Architect:  remember, not all machines are ambivalent towards humans, indeed some of them cherish humans as the creators of the machines.  The Architect built the Matrix, and when the anomoly arose (which he was unable to eliminate) he allows the Oracle to ply her prophecy program so that the One and the liberated humans of Zion are ultimately destroyed such that the Matrix is rebooted, it all starts again and the machines can keep using people as batteries.<br>
<br>
You mention &quot;Ghost&quot;.  You're referring to the character in the video game.  The character you are referring to in the movie is &quot;Seraph&quot;.  Despite your being agnostic and choosing to ignore the spiritual implications of the Matrix - of which there are many spiritual, philsophical and religious symbols - the Wachowski brothers have many spiritual devices in the movie.  A seraph or seraphim represents the highest order of angels, which also ties into Seraph's gold code coloration as angels are often spoken of as coming in glory or appearing in light etc...  <br>
<br>
If you recall what Seraph stated &quot;I guard that which is most important&quot; and the fact that he was able to access all of those backdoor with just one key (even the Keymaster needed a bunch of them), I think it's safe to say that Seraph is definitely a higher power, something of a guardian angel.<br>
<br>
The puzzling thing is the end sequence with Neo stopping the sentinels and whatever happened to Smith's avatar in the real world.  Guess we'll have to wait until November to find out!<br>
