<br>
However I am faced with a puzzling question:<br>
<br>
The Architect presents Neo with two choices:  1 - one door foresakes Trinity in order to &quot;save&quot; Zion and 2 - the other door seeks to save Trinity but foresakes the whole of Neo's race (both those in the Matrix and those in Zion).<br>
<br>
The question is this:  what was the other choice that the previous One's had to make if none of the previous One's were confronted by love?<br>
<br>
While the Oracle states in the first film that Neo will fall in love, it is also stated in Reload that the previous One's DID NOT have to deal with making a choice over a loved one...hence I am confused as to what the Architect's choices would have been for the previous One's...<br>
<br>
Now, in regards to the Architect's confidence that Neo would foresake Trinity to save Zion, it makes perfect sense.  On a logical level, the Architect is the perfect computer, who seeks and is governed by logic, mathematics and reason.  On a moral level, the parallel between Satan and the Architect has also been made.  On either level (as Satan or a computer), the Architect (nor any machine for that matter) would truly understand the implications of love.  <br>
<br>
The Architect improperly predicts Neo's reaction to the choice (remember, he talks about the emotional build-up that Neo is feeling, the feeling that he must foresake Trinity and that she is already dead), because to a logical or diabolic entity, sacrificing all of humanity for the sake of one person is completely illogical.<br>
<br>
That is the turning point for Neo in comparison to the other One's.  The other One's made the &quot;logical&quot; choice, which is the gaurded path of the Matrix itself, and accordingly never step beyond the bonds of control imposed by the machines.  By embracing love and sacrificing everything for the sake of love, Neo's evolves spiritually - this has been likened to Christ sacrificing himself for the love of humanity (despite the temptations that Satan presented him), which in turn lead to the salvation of himself and all of humanity.<br>
<br>
Whether the 3rd installment expands on that aspect of it...who knows.  There is religious parable throughout the story of the Matrix, and there is no uncertainty that Neo = Christ on the certain level.<br>
<br>
Personally, I think the the secret to how Neo EMP'd the squids relates to Smith.  The two are the Ying and Yang of the Matrix and are becoming ever more, inexorably tied together.<br>
<br>
Accordingly, I can see the two of them coming to some sort of reconcilliation that will be pivotal to the freedom of man and machine from a mutual relationship of slavery, into one of harmony.<br>
<br>
So much to this movie. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whistlerfv>Whistler FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mod in disguise</span><br>  Posts: 305<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/21/03 5:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1566.topic&index=30>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Yeeeeaah ...  8^p</span><hr size=1> Heh, did *any* of you read the link I posted?   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
