<br>
Two theories:<br>
<br>
1 - presuming that Zion is still within the Matrix (i.e. not really real), then the whole One Prophecy and Zion are just another form of control to catch that percentage of the population that rejects the &quot;1999 Matrix&quot;.  While the Architect cannot control who or when rejects the program, they can exercise control over where those people go.  So rather than having these &quot;rebels&quot; going this way and that, they all funnel into yet another program of control.<br>
<br>
2 - presuming that Zion is in fact the real world, then again the aim is to funnel those who reject the &quot;1999 Matrix&quot; into an area where they can be contained and dealt with.<br>
<br>
Personally, I have a difficult time with the concept that a real Zion has been destroyed and rebuilt 5 times - there are too many flaws with that concept (technology development, population growth, etc...) within the rough timeframe presented.  I suppose if the machines secretly aided in the restructuring of Zion, that might explain it, but it seems a little far fetched - even for the Matrix.<br>
<br>
I don't think that Zion being within the Matrix is unreasonable, but that presents the problem of &quot;where does it end?&quot;.<br>
<br>
When you get down to it, you'll find holes with any storyline like this because it presents the fantastic (i.e. based on our understanding of science and energy, humans would serve as LOUSY power sources, but it makes a cool story) so sometimes you just gotta go with it.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jaelyndimathe>Jaelyn DiMathe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of Truth</span><br>  Posts: 495<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/22/03 11:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1566.topic&index=38>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://myweb.cableone.net/agunders/jae.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Yeeeeaah ...  8^p</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>1 - presuming that Zion is still within the Matrix (i.e. not really real), then the whole One Prophecy and Zion are just another form of control to catch that percentage of the population that rejects the &quot;1999 Matrix&quot;. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
